This project automates key processes in an Educational Organization using ServiceNow Flow Designer. The goal is to streamline administrative workflows, reduce manual effort, and provide a seamless experience for staff, faculty, and students.
ðŸ”¹ Key Features
End-to-End Process Automation: Automates repetitive tasks across departments (Admissions, HR, IT, Library, Student Services).
Centralized Workflow Management: All requests and tasks are tracked in ServiceNow.
Notifications & Approvals: Automated approvals and alerts to ensure faster decision-making.
Integration Ready: Supports integration with Student Information Systems (SIS), Learning Management Systems (LMS), and HR systems.
Scalable: Can be customized for schools, colleges, or universities.
ðŸ”¹ Benefits
Reduces manual paperwork and delays in educational processes.
Improves collaboration across different departments.
Ensures transparency and accountability through ServiceNow dashboards.
Enhances overall student and faculty experience by automating routine services.
ðŸ”¹ Tech Stack
Platform: ServiceNow
Automation Tool: Flow Designer
Modules Used: Service Catalog, Notifications, Approvals, Task Management
ðŸ”¹ Example Use Cases
HR Automation: Faculty and staff onboarding/offboarding.
IT Services: Automated account creation, password resets, and access provisioning.
Student Services: Request handling (transcripts, certificates, ID cards).
Facilities: Classroom/lab allocation and maintenance requests.

